name: Bitope' | Cangrejo | Crab
description: Drawing in ink and paper by José Ángel Santiago, 2021 || My dad used to tell a story about a woman who lived in the sea that had crabs on top of her spine. Their claws would envelop her being at the same time her hands and legs. When harvest season was over she would lose her crabs and had the power to make any woman fertile || https://www.instagram.com/joseangelsantiago/
